  "title": "奉命谋杀",
  "source_file": "data\\raw\\detectiveqa\\novel_data_en\\252-奉命谋杀-阿加莎克里斯蒂.txt",
  "chunk_index": 39,
  "summary": "Philip and Gwendolyn discuss the possibility of marriage, though Gwendolyn expresses bitterness and resentment toward Rachel Agar, noting that Leo might be forced to remain Rachel's husband.\n\nIn a separate scene, Tina visits the well-tended grave of Mrs. Aigle in a new cemetery. While she is placing carnations on the tombstone, Mickey arrives. Mickey reveals he is leaving for a job at an oil company in three weeks and wanted to say goodbye to his mother to apologize for his past lack of appreciation and his previous unkindness toward her. During their conversation, Mickey denies killing his mother, a suspicion he believes Tina holds.\n\nTina then reveals that she was at Sunset Point on the night of the death. She explains that while she was walking back to her car, she heard two people whispering. One person specified a time between seven and seven-thirty and told the other not to mess up, followed by a response of \"You can trust me\" and a final comment that \"everything will be wonderful\" afterward. Tina cannot identify the voices but suspects it may have been a man and a woman. She suggests the conspirators could be Leo and Gwendolyn, or perhaps Hurst and someone else, but she explicitly rules out Philip. Tina also mentions seeing a shadow walk quickly past her and hearing a car start, noting that the figure could have been Mickey due to his height and build. Mickey insists he is not the killer and urges Tina to get into his car so he can drive her to Sunny Corner.",
